ng narrative of contemporary Egypt’s indigenous visual culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPhotographyxPolitical aspectszEgypt. 0aPhotographyzEgyptxHistory. 7aPhotography / History.2bisacsh  aArab Spring.  aEgyptian photography.  aNorth African cultures.  adecoloniality.  adecolonizing.  aimage politics.  amodernity.  aorientalism.  aphotographic criticism.  aphotography histories.  avisual censorship.1 aClose, Ronnie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2024 eBook-Packagez9783111332345oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616596140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526165961423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526165961/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPb2024